result.name: Kim's Kitchen

reviews.text: Nice food and reasonable price

Though it's not authentic, its food is not bad  and services are good.  Tried its lunch and fried chicken today: the rice bowl was delicious and fried chicken was juicy though I didn't like much about its seasoning.
Great food, super lunch set. I go pretty much every week

Based on the food Kim's Kitchen is barely a 1 out of 5. But at least the service was friendly and the staff tried their best. Thats way I am willing to extend some grace and place a 2 star. But unless there is a vast improvement in food quality don't go. Just don't go. The lamb looked like they cut it with a blender.  And the $300 prime beef rib-eye was served frozen!

Just found this place around the corner from my flat, and glad I did... Usually have to trek down to TST for decent Korean food. Lovely little traditional setup inside and upstairs. Tables ready for Korean BBQ. Had the lunch sets, Spicy Pork, Bulgolgi & Korean Cold Noodle. Super cheap prices, tasty selections...looking forward to more!

2nd visit, got the KFC tea set w/ fries & salad. Salad never showed, but the chicken was on the bone and crispy. Can't get enough of the Spicy Bulgogi Sauce!
